100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 8, 1925, tensions escalated in the Middle East as the British government faced growing unrest in Palestine amid Arab opposition to Jewish immigration. In the United States, the Senate continued debates on the proposed tariff bill, with strong opinions dividing Democrats and Republicans. Meanwhile, the trial of the Scopes "Monkey" case drew national attention, spotlighting the clash between modern science and traditional beliefs in education.
